==English==

===Etymology===
From {{AGr.}} '''{{polytonic|[[ἐσώτερoς]]}}''' (esōteros) "inner" (''esoteric'' originally referred to the secret (vs. public) teachings of Greek philosophers)

===Pronunciation===
*{{enPR|/ěsōtěr'ĭk/}}, {{IPA|/ˌɛsoˈtɛrɪk/}}, {{SAMPA|/EsoU"tErIc/}}
